Great — here’s a **sample policy** you can use or adapt for your company regarding **customers requesting quotes for graphic design services**:

---

### **Customer Quotation Request Policy**

**Effective Date:** \[Insert Date]
**Reviewed:** \[Insert Date]

#### **1. Purpose**

This policy outlines the procedure for customers requesting quotes for graphic design services to ensure clear communication, accurate pricing, and timely responses.

---

#### **2. Scope**

This policy applies to all clients or prospective clients seeking quotations for any design work provided by \[Your Company Name].

---

#### **3. Quotation Request Procedure**

**a. Initial Inquiry**
Customers may request a quote by:

- Filling out the Quote Request Form on our website
- Emailing us at \[email address]
- Calling our office at \[phone number]

**b. Required Information**
To receive an accurate quote, customers must provide the following:

- Project description (e.g., logo design, brochure, web graphics)
- Number of design assets required
- Preferred design style or inspiration
- Final format(s) needed (e.g., JPG, PDF, AI)
- Intended use (digital, print, commercial, etc.)
- Deadline or timeline
- Budget (optional but encouraged)

---

#### **4. Turnaround Time**

Quotes are typically provided within **2–3 business days** after receiving all required information. Delays may occur if the request lacks sufficient detail.

---

#### **5. Validity of Quote**

All quotations are valid for **30 calendar days** from the date issued, unless otherwise stated.

---

#### **6. Revisions and Clarifications**

If project requirements change after the initial quote, a revised quotation may be issued. We reserve the right to reassess timelines and pricing accordingly.

---

#### **7. Confidentiality**

All project details shared with us for quotation purposes will be treated as confidential and will not be disclosed without the customer’s consent.

---

#### **8. Acceptance**

To proceed with a project, customers must confirm acceptance of the quote in writing (via email or signed document). A deposit may be required before work begins.

---

Would you like this turned into a formatted PDF, or need help integrating this into your website or client onboarding documents?

<!-- --------------- Request for Quotation Form -------------------- -->

import React, { useState } from 'react';

const QuoteRequestForm = () => {
const [selectedService, setSelectedService] = useState('');

const handleServiceChange = (e) => {
setSelectedService(e.target.value);
};

return (

<form className="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-md space-y-6">
<h2 className="text-2xl font-bold text-center">Request a Quote</h2>

      {/* Basic Info */}
      <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div>
          <label className="block font-semibold">Full Name *</label>
          <input type="text" name="name" required className="input" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label className="block font-semibold">Company Name</label>
          <input type="text" name="company" className="input" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label className="block font-semibold">Email Address *</label>
          <input type="email" name="email" required className="input" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label className="block font-semibold">Phone Number</label>
          <input type="tel" name="phone" className="input" />
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Service Selector */}
      <div>
        <label className="block font-semibold">Type of Service *</label>
        <select
          name="service"
          required
          onChange={handleServiceChange}
          className="input"
        >
          <option value="">-- Select Service --</option>
          <option value="graphic_design">Graphic Design</option>
          <option value="packaging_design">Product Packaging Design</option>
          <option value="website_dev">Website Development / Hosting</option>
          <option value="data_analysis">Data Analysis</option>
        </select>
      </div>

      {/* Conditional Sections */}
      {selectedService === 'graphic_design' && (
        <div className="service-section">
          <h3 className="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Graphic Design Details</h3>
          <input type="text" name="graphic_type" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Design Type & Quantity" />
          <input type="text" name="graphic_dimensions" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Dimensions & Format" />
          <textarea name="graphic_style" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Preferred Style or References" />
          <input type="date" name="graphic_deadline" className="input mb-2" />
          <input type="file" name="graphic_assets" multiple className="input" />
        </div>
      )}

      {selectedService === 'packaging_design' && (
        <div className="service-section">
          <h3 className="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Packaging Design Details</h3>
          <input type="text" name="packaging_product" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Product Type & Dimensions" />
          <textarea name="packaging_specs" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Material & Print Specifications" />
          <textarea name="packaging_content" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Content to Include" />
          <input type="date" name="packaging_deadline" className="input mb-2" />
          <input type="file" name="packaging_assets" multiple className="input" />
        </div>
      )}

      {selectedService === 'website_dev' && (
        <div className="service-section">
          <h3 className="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Website Development Details</h3>
          <input type="text" name="website_purpose" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Website Purpose" />
          <input type="text" name="website_pages" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Estimated Number of Pages" />
          <textarea name="website_features" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Required Features" />
          <select name="website_hosting" className="input mb-2">
            <option value="">Need Hosting and Domain?</option>
            <option value="yes">Yes</option>
            <option value="no">No</option>
          </select>
          <input type="date" name="website_deadline" className="input mb-2" />
          <input type="file" name="website_assets" multiple className="input" />
        </div>
      )}

      {selectedService === 'data_analysis' && (
        <div className="service-section">
          <h3 className="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Data Analysis Details</h3>
          <textarea name="analysis_goal" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Project Goal / Questions to Answer" />
          <input type="text" name="data_format" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Data Source Format" />
          <input type="text" name="data_tools" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Preferred Tools" />
          <textarea name="data_deliverables" className="input mb-2" placeholder="Expected Deliverables" />
          <input type="date" name="data_deadline" className="input mb-2" />
          <input type="file" name="data_upload" multiple className="input" />
        </div>
      )}

      {/* Additional Notes */}
      <div>
        <label className="block font-semibold">Additional Notes</label>
        <textarea name="additional" className="input" />
      </div>

      <div>
        <label className="block font-semibold">Estimated Budget</label>
        <input type="text" name="budget" className="input" />
      </div>

      <button type="submit" className="w-full mt-4 bg-blue-600 text-white font-semibold py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition">
        Submit Request
      </button>
    </form>

);
};

export default QuoteRequestForm;
